Sergio:

The PRG pattern Seb mentions is also a very nice way to support &quot;stored&quot;
queries if that is a possible feature. Using POST can result in creating
shared or user-specific queries that can be listed and replayed at some
future point:

# request
POST /query
...
&lt;body of search args&gt;

# response
201 Created
Location: /query/user1/1

# request
GET /query/user1/1

# response
200 OK
...

# request
GET /query/user1/
...
&lt;query-list&gt;
  &lt;link href=&quot;..&quot; rel=&quot;self&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;link href=&quot;/query/user1/1&quot; rel=&quot;http://example.org/rels/query&quot; ... /&gt;
  &lt;link href=&quot;/query/user1/2&quot; rel=&quot;http://example.org/rels/query&quot; ... /&gt;
  ...
&lt;/query-list&gt;

